Text: Peaceful NightTime routine, new sounds and garden needs
Notes:
Today we had an interesting shift in behavior.
Last night Mara refused to stay asleep after rocking and walking around, she would wake as soon as we put her down.
Then, daddy left us - he's sleeping downstairs for a few nights to try to catch up on some much needed sleep now that he's working again.
The rest of the night we did the sweetest tandem dance between the bed and the co-sleeper: nurse, get drowsy, move to co-sleeper, sleep a full 1h15 min cycle, repeat.
No rocking or carrying our bouncing, just peaceful routine! We got upset twice because of wet diapers, but that got resolved quickly.
Now if only we could convince her to stay asleep for two cycles in a row! Hopefully after what seems to be a little growth spurt going on...

In the daytime we had two successful naps where she just winked out on her own soon after nursing to fullness. However for the 5 pm nap we struggled a lot and kept waking :-/. Possible causes: pool water fountain stopped around 4:30pm and we had no white noise going on. Tomorrow we'll try to add some background soothing sounds and see.

New milestones of the day:
Daddy called us at noon and after 3 minutes Mara "decided" to hung up on him with her little left fistie!
We heard something completely new to Mara: a ton of chirps all day from our new-and-improved canary bird Galben that got back from the vet after surgery to remove an awfully hurting stuck feather. Galben is so much more lovely now, but as a result he sang our ears off and startled us during our naps.
After a garden outing with daddy yesterday, Mara wanted it again really badly, and would complain when we were trying to get back to get the sling. We went out the front door and she looked really curiously at our olive tree!!

We heard something completely new to Mara: a ton of chirps all day from our new-and-improved canary bird Galben that got back from the vet after surgery to remove an awfully hurting stuck feather. Galben is so much more happy now, and in thanks he filled our ears with songs that kinda disturbed our naps.
woke up when we moved to the mat
Mara wanted really badly some time outside! we checked out the backyard and even went out front! she took long looks at the huge olive tree at our front door.
